---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { galaxies, manifest } from "../../lib/data";
---
<BaseLayout title="Dataset" description="HUGIN dataset schema, versions, artifacts and download information.">
  <header class="wrap section"><p class="eyebrow">Static public dataset</p><h1>Versioned, inspectable, reproducible.</h1><p class="lede">GitHub Actions normalizes the owner import, computes semantic neighborhoods, prepositions the galaxies and publishes immutable hashed assets. The browser performs no AI inference.</p></header>
  <section class="wrap" style="padding-bottom:70px">
    <div class="metrics"><div class="metric"><strong>{manifest.datasetVersion}</strong><span>dataset version</span></div><div class="metric"><strong>{manifest.schemaVersion}</strong><span>schema version</span></div><div class="metric"><strong>{manifest.counts.uniqueBodies.toLocaleString()}</strong><span>deduplicated bodies</span></div><div class="metric"><strong>64</strong><span>content shards</span></div></div>
    <div class="entity-grid"><article class="prose"><h2>Public contracts</h2><p>The catalog contains stable IDs, unique slugs, permanent routes, structural galaxy membership, body references and sanitized provenance. Relations record their origin so generated similarity can never be confused with curated research.</p><h2>Downloads</h2><p>Versioned JSONL, CSV and GraphML snapshots, metrics and SHA-256 checksums are published through <a href="https://github.com/PrinceOfPwn/Hugin/releases">GitHub Releases</a>.</p><h2>Similarity model</h2><p><code>{manifest.similarityModel}</code><br /><code>{manifest.similarityRevision}</code></p></article><aside class="sidebar card"><p class="eyebrow">Source integrity</p><p><small>Corpus SHA-256</small><br /><code>{manifest.sourceHash}</code></p><p><small>Build commit</small><br /><code>{manifest.commit}</code></p></aside></div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
